{"type":"text","timestamp":1775852550234,"sessionID":"ses_286f20e01ffecsCzehmYTMZYjX","part":{"id":"prt_d790f7543001oCSFObA8iwhrPo","messageID":"msg_d790f67e2001JOFhtOZYdxttEt","sessionID":"ses_286f20e01ffecsCzehmYTMZYjX","type":"text","text":"I see there's already a `proposal.md` file for AR-011. I should create the proposal in the appropriate location following the existing project structure. Let me check the changes directory structure:","time":{"start":1775852550232,"end":1775852550232}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775852587890,"sessionID":"ses_286f20e01ffecsCzehmYTMZYjX","part":{"id":"prt_d790f785b001FegvF0bmSZ4B14","messageID":"msg_d790f67e2001JOFhtOZYdxttEt","sessionID":"ses_286f20e01ffecsCzehmYTMZYjX","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_b2fc32f8905c45f7a7111294","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Proposal: Session Storage Interface Implementation (AR-012)\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement a session storage interface in `pkg/store` that provides Redis and Valkey backends for persisting sandbox metadata, with indexed queries for garbage collection based on expiry and last-activity timestamps.\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe session storage system provides persistent storage for sandbox session metadata in the agentcube project. It enables:\n\n1. **Session persistence**: Store and retrieve sandbox information keyed by session ID\n2. **Garbage collection support**: Index sessions by expiry time and last activity for cleanup operations\n3. **Backend flexibility**: Support both Redis and Valkey storage providers via configuration-based selection\n4. **Singleton access**: Thread-safe initialization and global access pattern\n\nThis implementation is required for AR-012 and supports the broader sandbox orchestration system documented in `sandbox-orchestration/design.md`.\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n- `pkg/store/store.go` - Core `Store` interface definition and `ErrNotFound` error\n- `pkg/store/singleton.go` - Singleton pattern with `Storage()` and `initStore()` functions\n- `pkg/store/store_redis.go` - Redis implementation using `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`\n- `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` - Valkey implementation using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`\n- Environment variable configuration for both backends\n- Index maintenance for expiry and last-activity sorted sets\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Database migration logic (stateless key-value store)\n- Horizontal scaling considerations for cluster deployments (noted in Valkey MGET slot comment)\n- Custom expiration hooks beyond index queries\n- Alternative storage backends (e.g., etcd, Consul)\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | Redis client library |\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Valkey client library |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | `SandboxInfo` type definitions |\n\n### Affected Components\n\n1. **Sandbox Orchestrator**: Will use `Storage()` to persist sandbox creation/update/delete operations\n2. **Garbage Collector**: Will use `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `ListInactiveSandboxes` for cleanup\n3. **Session Manager**: Will use `UpdateSessionLastActivity` for activity tracking\n\n### Backward Compatibility\n\n- This is a new module with no existing API contracts\n- No migration required (stateless store initialization)\n\n### Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|------------|\n| Redis/Valkey connection failures | Medium | `Ping()` method for health checks; connection retry logic in client libraries |\n| ZSET index inconsistency | Low | Atomic pipeline operations in `StoreSandbox` and `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` |\n| Password misconfiguration | Medium | Clear error messages on initialization failure; `*_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` escape hatch |\n| Valkey cluster slot conflicts | Low | Document in `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` that keys must be in same slot |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Single Backend (Redis Only)\n\n**Approach**: Implement only Redis support initially\n\n**Pros**:\n- Simpler codebase\n- Faster initial implementation\n- Reduced testing surface\n\n**Cons**:\n- Limits deployment flexibility\n- Valkey provides better performance characteristics for some workloads\n- May require refactor later if Valkey support becomes critical\n\n**Decision**: Implement both backends in parallel to avoid future refactoring and support diverse deployment scenarios.\n\n### Alternative 2: Interface-per-Backend Pattern\n\n**Approach**: Define separate interfaces for Redis and Valkey instead of a common `Store` interface\n\n**Pros**:\n- Backend-specific optimizations easier to implement\n- No abstraction leakage\n\n**Cons**:\n- Caller code must branch on backend type\n- Violates dependency inversion principle\n- Makes testing harder\n\n**Decision**: Use a common `Store` interface to enable transparent backend swapping and simplify caller code.\n\n### Alternative 3: TTL-Based Expiration Only\n\n**Approach**: Rely solely on Redis/Valkey native TTL instead of maintaining `session:expiry` ZSET\n\n**Pros**:\n- Simpler implementation\n- Leverages built-in expiration\n\n**Cons**:\n- Cannot query \"sessions expiring before time X\" efficiently\n- Last-activity tracking still requires ZSET\n- Inconsistent semantics between expiry and activity\n\n**Decision**: Maintain explicit ZSET indices for both expiry and last-activity to support efficient range queries required by garbage collection.\n\n### Alternative 4: Hash vs. JSON String Storage\n\n**Approach**: Store session data as Redis Hash instead of JSON string\n\n**Pros**:\n- Partial field updates possible\n- More \"Redis-native\"\n\n**Cons**:\n- Complex nested structures (e.g., `EntryPoints` array) awkward in hashes\n- JSON marshaling already required for `SandboxInfo` type\n- Less portable across Redis/Valkey client libraries\n\n**Decision**: Use JSON string storage for simplicity and consistency with `SandboxInfo` type serialization.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Core Interface and Types\n\n1. Define `Store` interface with exact method signatures\n2. Define `ErrNotFound` sentinel error\n3. Implement `SandboxInfo` and `SandboxEntryPoint` types in `pkg/common/types` (if not already present)\n\n### Phase 2: Singleton Pattern\n\n1. Implement `singleton.go` with `sync.Once` initialization\n2. Implement provider selection logic based on `STORE_TYPE`\n3. Add fatal logging on initialization failure\n\n### Phase 3: Redis Implementation\n\n1. Implement `redisStore` struct with key pattern constants\n2. Implement `makeRedisOptions` for environment variable parsing\n3. Implement all interface methods using Redis commands per spec\n4. Add pipeline/atomic operations for `StoreSandbox` and `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`\n\n### Phase 4: Valkey Implementation\n\n1. Implement `valkeyStore` struct mirroring Redis structure\n2. Implement `makeValkeyOptions` with cluster-aware options\n3. Implement all interface methods using Valkey fluent API\n4. Add MGET optimization in `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs`\n\n### Phase 5: Testing\n\n1. Unit tests for each backend with mocked clients\n2. Integration tests with real Redis and Valkey instances (Docker-based)\n3. Test password-required vs. password-optional scenarios\n4. Test ZSET index consistency under concurrent operations\n\n---\n\n## Configuration Reference\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Backend | Required | Default | Notes |\n|----------|---------|----------|---------|-------|\n| `STORE_TYPE` | Both | No | `redis` | Case-insensitive: `redis` or `valkey` |\n| `REDIS_ADDR` | Redis | Yes | - | Host:port format |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Redis | Conditional | - | Required unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | Redis | No | `true` | Case-insensitive boolean |\n| `VALKEY_ADDR` | Valkey | Yes | - | Comma-separated cluster addresses |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Valkey | Conditional | - | Required unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | Valkey | No | `true` | Case-insensitive boolean |\n| `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | Valkey | No | `false` | Enable to set `DisableCache=true` |\n| `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | Valkey | No | `false` | Enable to set `ForceSingleClient=true` |\n\n---\n\n## Key Design Decisions\n\n1. **Pipeline Atomicity**: `StoreSandbox` and `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` use Redis pipelines / Valkey `DoMulti` to ensure atomic index updates\n\n2. **NotFound Semantics**: Both backends normalize their native \"nil\" responses to `ErrNotFound` for consistent caller handling\n\n3. **UpdateSandbox Validation**: Uses `SET XX` to enforce \"key must exist\" semantics, preventing accidental creation\n\n4. **List Tolerance**: `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `ListInactiveSandboxes` skip orphaned ZSET members rather than failing the entire batch\n\n5. **Last-Activity Precondition**: `UpdateSessionLastActivity` requires the session key to exist, returning `ErrNotFound` if absent\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `Store` interface matches exact signatures from spec\n- [ ] Redis implementation passes all command patterns from spec table\n- [ ] Valkey implementation passes all API patterns from spec table\n- [ ] `Storage()` singleton initializes exactly once under concurrent access\n- [ ] Provider selection respects `STORE_TYPE` case-insensitivity\n- [ ] Password-optional mode works for both backends\n- [ ] ZSET indices remain consistent after store/update/delete operations\n- [ ] `ErrNotFound` returned consistently for missing sessions\n- [ ] All environment variables documented and tested\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Design: `session-store/design.md`\n- Specification: `session-store/spec.md`\n- Client-Go: `deployment/client-go.md`\n- Sandbox Orchestration: `sandbox-orchestration/design.md`\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-012/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-012/proposal.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-012/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775852587879,"end":1775852587888}}}}
